{"name":"Generate social posts with Airtable and WordPress with instant alerts","nodes":[{"parameters":{"rule":{"interval":[{"field":"hours","hoursInterval":1}]}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.scheduleTrigger","typeVersion":1.2,"position":[-270,400],"id":"c62fb04d-662d-43cb-af6b-b54bf3e14312","name":"Hourly Schedule"},{"parameters":{"method":"GET","url":"https://api.example.com/v1/drafts","options":{"timeout":20000},"sendQuery":true,"queryParameters":{"parameters":[{"name":"updated_since","value":"={{ $now.minus({hours: 6}).toISO() }}"},{"name":"limit","value":"100"}]}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest","typeVersion":4.2,"position":[54,400],"id":"1693041f-50c5-4e5d-a653-e10c9c4d37f6","name":"Pull Fresh Items (API)","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"sortFieldsUi":{"sortField":[{"fieldName":"tone","order":"descending"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.sort","typeVersion":1,"position":[378,400],"id":"bbec0511-142d-4876-89bc-f34220a389b4","name":"Newest First"},{"parameters":{"maxItems":15},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.limit","typeVersion":1,"position":[702,400],"id":"660a91a9-2194-4c8b-85ba-12c814a3d106","name":"Trim to Digest Size"},{"parameters":{"options":{}},"type":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainSummarization","typeVersion":2,"position":[1026,400],"id":"ab54e8f8-8ec3-4e92-9104-a82b7959f34d","name":"Summarize Content (AI)","onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"model":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"gpt-4o-mini","cachedResultName":"gpt-4o-mini"},"options":{}},"type":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatOpenAi","typeVersion":1.2,"position":[1269,970],"id":"468f0138-642e-42da-b0d9-6e9abed3dbe5","name":"OpenAI Chat Model"},{"parameters":{"mode":"markdownToHtml","markdown":"={{ $json.response?.text || $json.text }}","options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.markdown","typeVersion":1,"position":[1593,400],"id":"0ed47681-5434-4ed8-9b8c-d13040fb6542","name":"Render as HTML"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#content","cachedResultName":"#content"},"text":"={{ $json.html || $json.response?.text || $json.text }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[1917,400],"id":"67ccc25f-8973-446b-abb2-96ff8d50c8c1","name":"Post Digest to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Draft Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[2241,400],"id":"cf682b63-7a4c-4b8d-a886-4f4f01879ed6","name":"Archive Digest in Google Sheets","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"operation":"csv","options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.convertToFile","typeVersion":1.1,"position":[2565,400],"id":"4afe0f77-c6be-44e4-886a-e969a9b95f08","name":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"operation":"create","base":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Content Generation Base"},"table":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Drafts"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.airtable","typeVersion":2.1,"position":[2889,400],"id":"ef51266a-2cd8-4532-ac93-969228bfabbd","name":"Archive Row Snapshot","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"method":"GET","url":"https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup","sendQuery":true,"queryParameters":{"parameters":[{"name":"query","value":"={{ $json.topic }}"}]},"options":{"timeout":15000}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest","typeVersion":4.2,"position":[3213,400],"id":"f865b6f3-f81a-4a77-a29b-1d547fb31196","name":"Enrich with Reference Data","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"alwaysOutputData":true,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"ee0f50cf-de2c-4569-b82e-ef7f6152d080","name":"enrichedAt","value":"={{ $now.toISO() }}","type":"string"},{"id":"67df7561-9319-4a0d-9c30-0f0b9f5d31f4","name":"enrichmentSource","value":"reference-api","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[3537,400],"id":"9598300c-f72c-454c-a02a-8b6b4622e229","name":"Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"mode":"runOnceForAllItems","jsCode":"// Build a stable idempotency key per draft (djb2 hash, no deps)\nfunction hash(s) {\n  let h = 5381;\n  for (let i = 0; i < s.length; i++) h = ((h << 5) + h + s.charCodeAt(i)) >>> 0;\n  return h.toString(16);\n}\nreturn $input.all().map(item => {\n  const j = item.json;\n  return { json: { ...j, idempotencyKey: hash([j.draftId, j.topic].join('|')) } };\n});"},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.code","typeVersion":2,"position":[3861,400],"id":"83e45a06-6562-4417-8ec7-b1f4b8cb1481","name":"Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"operation":"removeItemsSeenInPreviousExecutions","logic":"removeItemsWithAlreadySeenKeyValues","dedupeValue":"={{ $json.idempotencyKey }}","options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.removeDuplicates","typeVersion":2,"position":[4185,400],"id":"52e25933-7ed6-4b20-842d-15eb87def668","name":"Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"operation":"getCurrentDate","outputFieldName":"completedAt","options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.dateTime","typeVersion":2,"position":[4509,400],"id":"0e617830-3bb6-42c1-82e8-8f4a28a93ccd","name":"Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"dataToSave":{"values":[{"key":"runId","value":"={{ $execution.id }}"},{"key":"itemCount","value":"={{ $items().length }}"}]}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.executionData","typeVersion":1,"position":[4833,400],"id":"4e852d62-4fb6-45a9-a168-1f96ea5da700","name":"Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"9573f428-fe12-401d-8ab4-02947ec9b265","name":"runAt","value":"={{ $now.toISO() }}","type":"string"},{"id":"6c3233e7-1b4f-425a-ace0-59bccf2167ce","name":"itemCount","value":"={{ $input.all().length }}","type":"number"},{"id":"9ba11b77-b9d2-4c42-a2e9-86491986bd20","name":"status","value":"completed","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[5157,400],"id":"7210d530-5eff-4392-bca9-ec3d2a920788","name":"Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"operation":"create","base":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Content Generation Base"},"table":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Drafts"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.airtable","typeVersion":2.1,"position":[5481,400],"id":"79672bfe-4c9d-43bf-b749-fbc73d5cf0bf","name":"Append Audit Row (Airtable)","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#content","cachedResultName":"#content"},"text":"=✅ Generate social posts with Airtable and WordPress with instant alerts — run completed at {{ $now.toFormat('HH:mm') }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[5805,400],"id":"89eef26f-f2f5-472e-b2a5-aa5007a4d6fa","name":"Send Summary to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"d9885c9f-049a-4b92-adea-1fadd94d5d37","name":"failedNode","value":"={{ $json.error?.node?.name || 'unknown' }}","type":"string"},{"id":"fd9a010a-fcd2-4ebd-aa1e-dabf0b5dd4bc","name":"errorMessage","value":"={{ $json.error?.message || JSON.stringify($json).slice(0,200) }}","type":"string"},{"id":"83b9c9d5-f195-46e7-9581-4b7549d7fdce","name":"workflow","value":"={{ $workflow.name }}","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[5157,1420],"id":"fbec0219-a510-4439-9fed-32a4d7e6e5f9","name":"Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#content","cachedResultName":"#content"},"text":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[5481,1420],"id":"693e6692-3781-4c1a-a054-b568fe498506","name":"Escalate Failure to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Draft Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[5805,1420],"id":"46e4fa32-6d3c-4c24-b8ef-83c686fe5422","name":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Hourly Schedule\n\nStarts the workflow on a timer — every 1 h. No input data; downstream nodes fetch what they need.\n\nNext: Pull Fresh Items (API)","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"7d34fd38-c07c-b20b-e87b-866fb0655ec5","name":"Note: Hourly Schedule"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Pull Fresh Items (API)\n\nGET https://api.example.com/v1/drafts — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Newest First · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"64d5f9cc-6532-f3a9-c8b9-f5628fc8c534","name":"Note: Pull Fresh Items (API)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Newest First\n\nOrders items (newest first) so limits and digests pick the most relevant records.\n\nNext: Trim to Digest Size","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"7e3d2bbe-9268-361d-0321-89ec5ff461f9","name":"Note: Newest First"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Trim to Digest Size\n\nCaps the stream at 15 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Summarize Content (AI)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"5807b76b-1a03-c728-b8d0-089cc3634882","name":"Note: Trim to Digest Size"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Content (AI)\n\nMap-reduce summarization chain — handles long content without blowing the context window.\n\nPorts: ①→ Render as HTML · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,520],"id":"3a491dad-21b6-604d-1863-84120f8a117d","name":"Note: Summarize Content (AI)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### OpenAI Chat Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `gpt-4o-mini`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Summarize Content (AI)** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 OpenAI API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1209,1090],"id":"bed3ad44-2785-0ebd-e84e-f2cfb940a62f","name":"Note: OpenAI Chat Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Render as HTML\n\nConverts markdown to HTML for rich rendering in email/CMS.\n\nNext: Post Digest to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1533,520],"id":"18fd1780-55e7-690c-403b-297fa1eb047c","name":"Note: Render as HTML"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Post Digest to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Archive Digest in Google Sheets · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1857,520],"id":"e51f5dac-43b6-d57b-3a6c-b511d2908026","name":"Note: Post Digest to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Digest in Google Sheets\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Serialize Run Output (CSV) · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2181,520],"id":"56e756a6-a6e9-2a24-cd01-f1e48766b58d","name":"Note: Archive Digest in Google Sheets"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2505,520],"id":"77b607e2-efa1-4d78-7784-e2a3908afdee","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\nairtable — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Enrich with Reference Data · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Airtable PAT","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2829,520],"id":"2f29d3e1-5180-7afe-d471-9ac277d2e931","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3153,520],"id":"a9de95e7-59bf-778e-d4d8-4a42294ccdb7","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Fingerprint for Idempotency","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3477,520],"id":"dadb5edd-886f-5e2d-062d-6468f268c40b","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per draft (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3801,520],"id":"683cd3df-2271-057b-2436-d64c2228d022","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4125,520],"id":"69f6c989-8951-8618-b565-71cd938c2629","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4449,520],"id":"734041a5-e785-bd55-24cb-7d97a67041e1","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4773,520],"id":"047f031f-5cfe-9520-09fe-e83f553e40e0","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Airtable)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5097,520],"id":"8ef3f037-465c-f9da-14f7-665bce5fe8b3","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Airtable)\n\nairtable — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Airtable PAT","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5421,520],"id":"b27e55d8-0607-ac7a-cf6f-c0a1a7db246c","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Airtable)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5745,520],"id":"fbfd6459-1b58-3560-089a-15f704024f4c","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5097,1540],"id":"a825f3c5-f750-1824-1e02-e2f86d05163b","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5421,1540],"id":"725291e8-de64-4535-8f36-adcca597762c","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5745,1540],"id":"fadaf48b-3d11-40db-c349-e205eb00742d","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Generate social posts with Airtable and WordPress with instant alerts\n\n**Pattern:** Content Generation · **Level:** Production · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nGenerate social posts with Airtable and WordPress with instant alerts. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual social copy is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Pull Fresh Items (API) → Newest First → Trim to Digest Size → Summarize Content (AI) → Render as HTML → Post Digest to Slack → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to content generation without manual effort\n- Anyone automating social copy in content creation\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Improves response time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Airtable PAT; Google OAuth2 / service account; OpenAI API key; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"b48f9879-637c-6758-1541-bc702b6e3c4c","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-20],"id":"3f8bbab5-c93d-0f63-599a-d24bee776454","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.","width":360,"height":260,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-20],"id":"3812cbb6-0fc5-3716-efe9-9651cd332fbe","name":"🤖 AI cluster"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-20],"id":"73e05508-a4f7-8d3a-273b-15a8c75d303a","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your social copy process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-20],"id":"3f83072e-775a-af36-05b3-79e04997d560","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Hourly Schedule":{"main":[[{"node":"Pull Fresh Items (API)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Pull Fresh Items (API)":{"main":[[{"node":"Newest First","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Newest First":{"main":[[{